  "prompt": "Which one is better: Royal Enfield Standard 350 or Classic 350?",
  "response": "Choosing between the Royal Enfield Standard 350 and the Classic 350 depends on your preferences and requirements, as both models have their own strengths.\n\n### Royal Enfield Standard 350\n\n#### Pros:\n1. **Simplicity and Tradition**: The Standard 350 is closer to the original Royal Enfield design, with a more utilitarian approach.\n2. **Timeless Design**: It retains a classic look that many traditionalists appreciate.\n3. **Affordable**: Generally, it might be slightly more affordable due to fewer premium features, depending on the market.\n\n#### Cons:\n1. **Fewer Features**: It lacks some of the modern features and comforts found in the Classic 350.\n2. **Less Variety**: Limited color and trim options compared to the Classic 350.\n\n### Royal Enfield Classic 350\n\n#### Pros:\n1. **Updated Features**: The Classic 350 often includes modern amenities like a more advanced instrument cluster and improved seating.\n2. **Aesthetic Appeal**: It is designed with a vintage look that includes retro finishes, attractive color options, and premium touches.\n3. **Comfort**: Typically offers a more comfortable ride with better riding ergonomics.\n\n#### Cons:\n1. **Price**: Usually priced higher due to the additional features and styling options.\n2. **Heavier**: Slightly heavier than the Standard 350, which may affect maneuverability.\n\n### Considerations:\n- **Purpose**: If you are looking for a daily commuter with a classic look and fewer fancy additions, the Standard 350 might suit you better.\n- **Style and Comfort**: If you prioritize aesthetics, comfort, and are interested in more features, the Classic 350 might be the better choice.\n- **Budget**: Consider your budget and whether the additional features of the Classic 350 justify the price difference for you.\n\nUltimately, test riding both models is the best way to determine which one fits your needs and preferences.",
